text:
CLEVELAND, Ohio – Cleveland police are investigating an overnight gunfight involving East Cleveland cops and a trio of robbery suspects, an official said.

An internal Cleveland Police document reveals the shooting occurred Tuesday near East 140th Street and Glenside Road about 9:30 pm. Cleveland officials have confirmed the incident is the result of a Tuesday night robbery at Sam's Deli on Hayden Avenue in East Cleveland.

East Cleveland police have refused to answer Northeast Ohio Media Group’s requests for details. They will not identify the suspects or provide specifics about the gunfire.

“They’re not really talking to anyone,” said Sgt. Ali Pillow, a Cleveland police spokesman. “We’re not sure yet how [East Cleveland police] ended up in Cleveland.”

Still, Cleveland police have been able to put some of the pieces together. Here is what they say they know:

• One of the robbery suspects was shot in the leg and treated at an area hospital;

• Two weapons were recovered after three suspects were arrested;

• Cleveland police apprehended one suspect, who was then arrested by East Cleveland police;

• East Cleveland police exchanged gunfire with at least one of the suspects during a foot pursuit;

• Cleveland officers were not involved in the shooting; and

• The Cleveland Division of Police Use of Deadly Force Investigation Team will review the incident – protocol when officers from any jurisdiction open fire in Cleveland.

Northeast Ohio Media Group will provide an update when information becomes available.
